Vice President Mike Pence met with President Juan Manuel Santos of Colombia to strengthen the relationship between the two countries. Pence thanked Santos for efforts to reduce coca cultivation and cocaine production, but emphasized the need for further action. They also discussed the use of chemical weapons in Syria and the United States' determination to prevent future attacks. The leaders also talked about Colombia's path to full OECD membership and their shared commitment to pressuring the Maduro regime in Venezuela to restore democracy.